---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';

// Required for static site generation - generates paths for all content
export function getStaticPaths() {
  // Content data defined here so it's accessible during static generation
  const contentData: Record<string, {
    title: string;
    pubDate: Date;
    tags: string[];
    content: string;
  }> = {
    'building-in-public': {
      title: 'Why I Started Building in Public',
      pubDate: new Date('2026-03-15'),
      tags: ['Personal', 'Strategy'],
      content: `Building in public has become a powerful movement among entrepreneurs and creators. When I first heard about it, I was skeptical - why would anyone share their failures and struggles openly?

## What Changed My Mind

After months of working in isolation on various projects, I realized that the journey matters more than the destination. Sharing the process, not just the results, creates authentic connections with others on similar paths.

**Key benefits I discovered:**
- Accountability pushes you to stay consistent
- Community support from startup founders
- Learning accelerates through feedback
- Building a reputation before you "need" one

## My Approach

I decided to start sharing my progress weekly, including lessons from failures, experiment results, and random thoughts on business and technology. The goal isn't perfection - it's showing up and being honest about the process.

## Looking Forward

This space will evolve as I do. I'm excited to connect with others who are building in public and share this journey together.`,
    },
    'ai-tools-small-business': {
      title: 'AI Tools for Small Business Automation',
      pubDate: new Date('2026-03-10'),
      tags: ['AI', 'Business', 'Automation'],
      content: `Small businesses often struggle with limited resources and time. AI tools can level the playing field, allowing small teams to accomplish what previously required larger staffs.

## Practical Applications

### Customer Service
- AI chatbots for instant responses
- Automated email responses
- FAQ generation

### Marketing
- Content generation assistance
- Social media scheduling
- Email campaign optimization

### Operations
- Data entry automation
- Appointment scheduling
- Inventory management

## Getting Started

You don't need to be a tech expert to use AI tools. Start small:

1. Identify one pain point in your business
2. Research AI solutions for that specific problem
3. Test with free trials
4. Scale what works

## My Experience

I've helped several local businesses implement AI tools with great results. The key is to focus on solving real problems, not just using AI for the sake of it.`,
    },
    'local-marketing-month-1': {
      title: 'Local Marketing Experiments - Month 1',
      pubDate: new Date('2026-03-01'),
      tags: ['Marketing', 'Experiments'],
      content: `I've been running marketing experiments for local businesses to understand what actually works versus what everyone says works.

## Month 1 Focus Areas

### Google Business Profile Optimization
- Updated all business information
- Added photos and posts regularly
- Encouraged customer reviews

### Local SEO
- Claimed and optimized directory listings
- Created local content
- Built local backlinks

### Social Media
- Tested Instagram, Facebook, and TikTok
- Focused on community engagement
- Ran small targeted ads

## Results

The consistency of showing up mattered more than any single tactic. Reviews have outsized impact on local rankings. Building genuine community connections creates sustainable growth.

## Key Learnings

1. Consistency beats virality
2. Reviews are gold for local rankings
3. Community first - local businesses thrive on genuine connections

## What's Next

Month 2 will focus on email marketing integration, referral programs, and partnership opportunities.`,
    },
    'first-business-failure': {
      title: 'Lessons from My First Business Failure',
      pubDate: new Date('2026-02-20'),
      tags: ['Business', 'Lessons'],
      content: `Every entrepreneur has a failure story. This is mine.

In 2018, I launched a digital product that I was convinced would change the way people managed their schedules. I was wrong.

## What Went Wrong

**Solving a Problem That Didn't Exist:** I built what I thought was a better calendar app. Turns out, people were already happy with their existing solutions.

**Ignoring User Feedback:** I was so attached to my vision that I dismissed early feedback that suggested the product wasn't resonating.

**Wrong Timing:** The market wasn't ready for another productivity tool. Everyone was moving toward simplicity, not more features.

## What I Learned

- Validation is everything - talk to users before building
- Be ready to pivot - your first idea is rarely your best
- Failure is data - each failure teaches you something valuable
- Keep going - most successful entrepreneurs failed multiple times

## Where I Am Now

That failure taught me more than any success could have. It shaped how I approach every project now - with humility, curiosity, and a willingness to iterate.`,
    },
    'ai-content-creation': {
      title: 'The Future of AI in Content Creation',
      pubDate: new Date('2026-02-15'),
      tags: ['AI', 'Content', 'Future'],
      content: `AI is transforming how content gets created, distributed, and consumed. This isn't science fiction - it's happening now.

## Current State

### What's AI Doing Well
- Drafting initial content versions
- Generating ideas and outlines
- Editing and proofreading
- Creating variations of existing content

### What AI Can't Do Yet
- Replace authentic human experience
- Understand nuanced cultural contexts
- Create truly original ideas
- Build genuine relationships

## The Hybrid Approach

The best content strategy combines AI for efficiency with humans for authenticity. Use AI as a drafting tool, not a replacement for your unique voice and perspective.

## Implications for Creators

**For Marketers:** Faster content production, personalization at scale, data-driven optimization.

**For Writers:** Overcome blank page syndrome, edit faster, focus on higher-level strategy.

**For Businesses:** Content at scale with consistent brand voice.

## The Future

Within 5 years, AI will be as common in content creation as spell-check is today. The creators who thrive will be those who learn to work with AI, not against it.`,
    },
  };

  return Object.keys(contentData).map((slug) => ({
    params: { slug },
    props: { content: contentData[slug] },
  }));
}

// Get content from props (passed by getStaticPaths)
const { content } = Astro.props;

// Format the publication date
const formattedDate = content.pubDate.toLocaleDateString('en-US', {
  year: 'numeric',
  month: 'long',
  day: 'numeric',
});

// Simple markdown-like parser for content
function parseContent(text: string): string {
  return text
    .split('\n\n')
    .map(paragraph => {
      // Headers
      if (paragraph.startsWith('## ')) {
        return `<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text mt-10 mb-4">${paragraph.slice(3)}</h2>`;
      }
      if (paragraph.startsWith('### ')) {
        return `<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text mt-8 mb-3">${paragraph.slice(4)}</h3>`;
      }
      // Bold text
      const boldFormatted = paragraph.replace(/\*\*([^*]+)\*\*/g, '<strong class="text-text font-semibold">$1</strong>');
      // Lists
      if (paragraph.includes('\n- ') || paragraph.startsWith('- ')) {
        const items = boldFormatted.split('\n').map(line => {
          if (line.startsWith('- ')) {
            return `<li class="text-muted ml-4 my-1">${line.slice(2)}</li>`;
          }
          return line;
        }).join('');
        return `<ul class="list-disc my-4 space-y-1">${items}</ul>`;
      }
      // Numbered lists
      if (paragraph.match(/^\d+\./m)) {
        const items = boldFormatted.split('\n').map(line => {
          const match = line.match(/^(\d+)\.\s*(.*)/);
          if (match) {
            return `<li class="text-muted ml-4 my-1"><span class="text-text font-medium">${match[1]}.</span> ${match[2]}</li>`;
          }
          return line;
        }).join('');
        return `<ol class="list-decimal my-4 space-y-1">${items}</ol>`;
      }
      // Regular paragraph
      if (paragraph.trim()) {
        return `<p class="text-muted my-4 leading-relaxed">${boldFormatted}</p>`;
      }
      return '';
    })
    .join('');
}
---

<Layout title={`${content.title} - Ayushman`} description={content.content.slice(0, 160)}>
  <Navbar />

  <main class="flex-1">
    {/* Article Header */}
    <header class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 border-b border-border">
      {/* Back Link */}
      <a
        href="/content"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-muted hover:text-text transition-colors mb-8"
      >
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" />
        </svg>
        Back to Content
      </a>

      {/* Tags */}
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
        {content.tags.map((tag: string) => (
          <span class="px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-muted bg-surface border border-border rounded-full">
            {tag}
          </span>
        ))}
      </div>

      {/* Title */}
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-text mb-4">
        {content.title}
      </h1>

      {/* Date */}
      <time class="text-sm text-muted">{formattedDate}</time>
    </header>

    {/* Article Body */}
    <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
      <div class="prose-content" set:html={parseContent(content.content)} />
    </article>

    {/* Article Footer */}
    <footer class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 border-t border-border">
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-4">
        <a
          href="/content"
          class="text-sm text-muted hover:text-text transition-colors"
        >
          &larr; Back to all content
        </a>

        {/* Share Links */}
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
          <span class="text-sm text-muted">Share:</span>
          <a
            href={`https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=${encodeURIComponent(content.title)}`}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-sm text-muted hover:text-text transition-colors"
          >
            Twitter
          </a>
          <a
            href={`https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url=${encodeURIComponent(Astro.url.href)}`}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-sm text-muted hover:text-text transition-colors"
          >
            LinkedIn
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
